# Common Terminal Commands Skill

Use this skill when the user asks for current public data, local diagnostics, app setup, or other tasks that can be answered by command-line tools.

## Core Rules

- Prefer the `terminal` tool for realtime data and verification.
- Do not use `web_search` for realtime values such as weather, prices, stock quotes, exchange rates, sports scores, package versions, or service status.
- `web_search` is only for fetching DuckDuckGo result links/snippets when the user needs links or source candidates.
- Read command output carefully. If a command fails, try one corrected command, then explain the blocker.
- Keep outputs concise in the final answer. Report the key result, timestamp/context, and any uncertainty.

## Windows Notes

- In PowerShell, `curl` can be an alias. Prefer `curl.exe` for real curl behavior.
- Quote URLs with `"` when they contain `?`, `&`, or spaces.
- For JSON APIs, use `Invoke-RestMethod` when available, or `curl.exe -s`.

## Weather

Use `wttr.in` for quick weather from terminal.

```powershell
curl.exe -s "https://wttr.in/Tokyo?format=3"
curl.exe -s "https://wttr.in/Tokyo?format=j1"
curl.exe -s "https://wttr.in/Tokyo?1"
curl.exe -s "https://wttr.in/Tokyo?m&format=%l:+%c+%t,+humidity+%h,+wind+%w"
```

For tomorrow's forecast, fetch JSON and summarize the `weather[1]` entry:

```powershell
Invoke-RestMethod "https://wttr.in/Tokyo?format=j1" | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 8
```

If the user does not provide a location, ask for a city or use terminal to infer approximate location from IP:

```powershell
curl.exe -s "https://ipinfo.io/json"
curl.exe -s "https://ipapi.co/json/"
```

## Public IP And Network

```powershell
curl.exe -s "https://api.ipify.org"
curl.exe -s "https://ifconfig.me"
Test-NetConnection example.com -Port 443
Resolve-DnsName example.com
```

## Time

```powershell
Get-Date
curl.exe -s "https://worldtimeapi.org/api/ip"
curl.exe -s "https://worldtimeapi.org/api/timezone/Asia/Tokyo"
```

## HTTP/API Checks

```powershell
curl.exe -I "https://example.com"
curl.exe -s "https://api.github.com/repos/OWNER/REPO/releases/latest"
Invoke-RestMethod "https://api.github.com/repos/OWNER/REPO/releases/latest"
```

## Package Versions

```powershell
npm view PACKAGE version
pnpm view PACKAGE version
python -m pip index versions PACKAGE
winget search PACKAGE
```

## Git And Repo State

```powershell
git status --short
git branch --show-current
git log -1 --oneline
git diff --stat
```

## Disk And System

```powershell
Get-ComputerInfo | Select-Object OsName, OsVersion, CsName
Get-PSDrive -PSProvider FileSystem
Get-Process | Sort-Object CPU -Descending | Select-Object -First 10
```
